  </p>
  <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mt-4 space-y-1">
    <li>The <strong>Federal Law on the Protection of Personal Data Held by Private Parties</strong> (Mexico)</li>
    <li>The <strong>General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)</strong> of the European Union</li>
    <li>The <strong>California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA)</strong> in the United States</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="mt-4">Below we provide you with important information regarding the collection, use, and protection of your personal data.</p>

  <hr class="my-8 border-t border-gray-300" />

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold">1. Data Collection</h3>
  <p class="mt-2">We may collect personal information at any of the contact and interaction points we have with our clients, including:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mt-2 space-y-1">
    <li>Our website and reservation system</li>
    <li>Information sent to or shared through our social media platforms</li>
    <li>Our internal systems and during your visit to the hotel</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="mt-2">This information may include:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mt-2 space-y-1">
    <li>Contact details (name, phone number, email, address)</li>
    <li>Information related to your booking, stay, or visit</li>
    <li>Payment data (credit card, TAX ID, business activity)</li>
    <li>Personal characteristics, nationality, passport or official ID number, and place and date of issue</li>
    <li>Travel history and preferences during your stay</li>
    <li>Data on travel companions (name, preferences)</li>
    <li>Medical information voluntarily provided to improve your experience</li>
    <li>Marketing and communication preferences</li>
    <li>Feedback and comments about our services</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-t border-gray-300" />

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold">2. Use of Personal and Sensitive Information</h3>
  <p class="mt-2">CASACANTA ZIHUA SA DE CV uses this information to provide the services you requested or those related to a reservation, transaction, or program. We may also use your data to:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mt-2 space-y-1">
    <li>Improve our services and offer the level of hospitality you expect</li>
    <li>Ensure that our website, products, and services meet your interests</li>
    <li>Process payments, refunds, and other service-related requests</li>
    <li>Send communications regarding services, promotions, and special events (with your prior consent)</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="mt-2">The legal basis for processing your data includes:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mt-2 space-y-1">
    <li>Your consent</li>
    <li>The execution of a contract (your reservation)</li>
    <li>Our legitimate interest (to improve services)</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="mt-2">All in accordance with applicable Mexican law, the GDPR, and the CCPA.</p>

  <hr class="my-8 border-t border-gray-300" />

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold">3. Data Transfers</h3>
  <p class="mt-2">We may transfer your personal data to:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mt-2 space-y-1">
    <li>IT service providers operating our technological infrastructure (servers, reservation systems, etc.)</li>
    <li>Medical providers, in case of emergency</li>
    <li>Competent authorities, when required by law</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="mt-2">If you do not object, we will assume that you authorize these transfers.</p>
  <p class="mt-2"><strong>Note for EU residents:</strong> We only transfer personal data outside the European Economic Area (EEA) to countries that ensure an adequate level of protection, or under Standard Contractual Clauses approved by the European Commission.</p>
  <p class="mt-2"><strong>Note for California residents (USA):</strong> We do not sell your personal information as defined under the CCPA.</p>

  <hr class="my-8 border-t border-gray-300" />

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold">4. Security Measures</h3>
  <p class="mt-2">We have implemented physical, technical, and administrative safeguards to protect your personal data from unauthorized access, loss, alteration, or misuse. These include:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mt-2 space-y-1">
    <li>SSL encryption on our website and reservation systems</li>
    <li>Internal access controls and staff training</li>
    <li>Secure backups and system monitoring</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-t border-gray-300" />

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold">5. ARCO Rights and Other Applicable Rights</h3>
  <p class="mt-2">In accordance with Mexican law, you have the right to Access, Rectify, Cancel, or Oppose the processing of your personal data (ARCO rights).</p>
  <p class="mt-2">Additionally, under GDPR and CCPA, you may also exercise the following rights:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mt-2 space-y-1">
    <li>Data portability (EU)</li>
    <li>Restriction of processing</li>
    <li>Right to erasure (“right to be forgotten”)</li>
    <li>Right to opt out of marketing or data sharing (California)</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="mt-2">You may submit your request to exercise any of these rights by writing to our Reservations and Sales Department: <a href="mailto:sales.reservations@lacasaquecanta.com" class="underline">sales.reservations@lacasaquecanta.com</a> · <a href="tel:+527555557000" class="underline">+52 (755) 555 7000</a></p>
  <p class="mt-2"><strong>Response Time:</strong> Within 20 business days from the date of receipt of your request, if it is deemed admissible, the corresponding action will be taken within 15 business days following the date on which the response is communicated.</p>
  <p class="mt-2">We will respond through the contact method you indicate in your request and within the timeframe established by applicable law.</p>

  <hr class="my-8 border-t border-gray-300" />

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold">6. Data Retention</h3>
  <p class="mt-2">We retain your personal data only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes described above, or as required by applicable tax or legal regulations.</p>

  <hr class="my-8 border-t border-gray-300" />

